# Platform Client Provisioning

The canonical onboarding script is `scripts/setup-new-client.mjs`.
It must always reflect the **exact** infrastructure every new client needs.

## Trigger: Update the script whenever you do any of the following

### Edge Functions
- Add or rename an edge function → add it to the `functions` array in step 13 of the script
- Remove an edge function → remove it from that array
- Edge functions are sourced from `apps/sweet-media/supabase/functions/` and deployed with `--workdir apps/sweet-media`
- Current deployed functions: `generate-blog-post`, `generate-blog-image`, `ping-google-indexing`, `inspect-google-indexing`

### Edge Function Secrets
- Add a new secret a function depends on → add it to the `secretParts` array in step 12
- Current secrets provisioned: `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `BLOG_IMAGE_BUCKET`, `BLOG_IMAGE_FOLDER`, `BLOG_WEBHOOK_SECRET`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_INDEXING_CLIENT_EMAIL`, `GOOGLE_INDEXING_PRIVATE_KEY`
- If a secret comes from `.env`, add a corresponding read from `loadEnvFile()` and a `warn()` if missing

### Schema Changes
- Any new table, column, index, or RLS policy change → update `apps/client-template/supabase/client-template-schema.sql`
- Also provide migration SQL for existing brands (inner-peak-colorado, sweet-media, mental-health-for-teens) so they can be brought up to date manually

### Storage Buckets
- Add a new bucket → add a creation block to step 10 of the script (pattern: retry loop with 409 check)
- Current buckets: `site-assets` (public)

### Vercel / Next.js Env Vars
- Add a new env var that every client app needs → add it to **`scripts/scaffold-client-app.mjs`** (`.env.local` lines) and the **`setup-new-client.mjs`** summary (step 15), so new apps get the same vars automatically.
- Current generated keys include: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ID`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`.

### App scaffold (Next.js)
- Companion script: **`scripts/scaffold-client-app.mjs`** (copy `apps/client-template` → `apps/<slug>`, package name, `next.config` Supabase host, `.env.local`, optional brand string replacement).
- **`setup-new-client.mjs`** runs it after fetching the anon key unless **`--no-scaffold`** is passed.

## Never
- Never assume a Supabase change made to one brand (e.g. sweet-media) is automatically live on another brand's project — each brand has its own Supabase project and must be provisioned independently
- Never skip updating this script just because the change was applied manually to an existing project — the script must always represent the full setup for a net-new client

## Existing Clients
Current live clients and their Supabase projects are managed independently.
When infrastructure diverges from the script, call it out and provide the exact manual steps to bring existing clients in sync.
